   <h2 align="center">Installation Plazma ERP+CRM</h2>
   <hr>
   <br><br><br><br>

   <h3 align="center">Hardware Requirements </h3>

   <b>Client</b><br><br>

   Processor: <font color="blue">Pentium 633 MHz or higher</font><br><br>

   Free Disk Space: <font color="blue">50 MB</font><br><br>

   RAM: <font color="blue">128 MB (256 MB recommended)</font><br><br>

   LAN adapter 10 Mb: <font color="blue">10 Mb (100 Mb recommended)</font><br><br>
   <br><br>


   <b>Server</b><br><br>

   Processor: <font color="blue">Pentium 1700 MHz or higher</font><br><br>

   Free Disk Space: <font color="blue">100 MB</font><br><br>

   RAM: <font color="blue">256 MB (512 MB recommended)</font><br><br>

   LAN adapter 10 Mb:  <font color="blue">10 Mb (100 Mb recommended)</font><br><br>
   <br><br>

   <b>Standalone</b><br><br>
   <font color="blue">
<b>This option is used for 1-3 workstations or demo mode</b></font>
   <br><br>


   Processor:  <font color="blue">Pentium 1700 MHz or higher</font><br><br>

   Free Disk Space: <font color="blue">50 MB</font><br><br>

   RAM: <font color="blue">128 MB (256 MB recommended)</font><br><br>

   LAN adapter 10 Mb: <font color="blue">10 Mb (100 Mb recommended)</font><br><br>

   <br><br><br><br>

   <h3 align="center">Software Requirements</h3>


   Operating system: <font color="blue">Windows, Linux, MacOS</font><br><br>

   Database: 
   <a target="_blank" href="http://www.oracle.com">Oracle 10g</a>, 
   <a target="_blank" href="http://www.postgresql.org">PostgreSQL 8.x</a>,
   <a target="_blank" href="http://www.mysql.org">MySQL 5.x</a>,
   <a target="_blank" href="http://www.firebirdsql.org">Firebird 1.5.3 or higher</a>,
   <a target="_blank" href="http://hsqldb.org">HSQL 1.7.2 or higher</a><br><br> 

  You need to have <b>JRE (Java Runtime Environment)</b> version <b>1.5</b> or 
  higher previously installed on your computer. 
  You can download last <b>JRE</b> <a target="_blank" href="http://java.com/getjava">here</a>. <br><br> 


   <br>
   <b>IMPORTANT!</b> The <b>Plazma ERP+CRM</b> installation includes only <b>HSQL</b> database.

   If you will use a different database, 
   you need to download and install the database server on your computer.

   <br><br><br><br>

   <h3 align="center">Installation Type</h3>


   <table width="100%">
   <tr>
     <td><b>#</b></td><td><b>Name</b></td><td><b>File name part</b></td><td><b>Description</b></td>
   </tr>
   <tr>
     <td>1</td><td>Standalone</td><td>-</td><td>Standalone (Client+Server)</td>
   </tr>
   <tr>
     <td>2</td><td>Client</td><td>client</td><td>Client part</td>
   </tr>
   <tr>
     <td>3</td><td>Server</td><td>server</td><td>Server part</td>
   </tr>
   </table>

<br>
<b>Option 1: Standalone</b> works <b>WITHOUT APPLICATION SERVER</b>, the client connects to the database server.
 Recommended for 1-3 workstations or demo mode.

<br><br>
The installation filename submitted in the form of:

<br><br>
plazma-&lt;installation type&gt;-&lt;version&gt;-&lt;operation system&gt;-installer.&lt;file extention&gt;

<br><br>
<code>&lt;file extention&gt;</code> -  <code>jar</code> or <code>exe</code>

   <br><br><br><br>


   <h3 align="center">Download</h3>


   You can download <b>Plazma ERP+CRM</b> installation from the site <a href="http://plazma.sourceforge.net">http://plazma.sourceforge.net</a> <br><br>


   Depending on the operating system and server technology to be used, you can choose various options for installation: 

   <br><br>

   <b>Windows (Standalone)</b> <br><br>


   <table width="100%">
   <tr>
     <td width="30"><b>#</b></td><td><b>File</b></td>
   </tr>
   <tr>
     <td>1</td><td>plazma-&lt;version&gt;-win32-installer.jar</td>
   </tr>
   <tr>
     <td>2</td><td>plazma-&lt;version&gt;-win32-installer.exe</td>
   </tr>
   <tr>
     <td>3</td><td>plazma-&lt;version&gt;-win32-jre-installer.exe</td>
   </tr>

   </table>


   <br><br>

   <b>Windows (Lite Server)</b> <br><br>


   <table width="100%">
   <tr>
     <td width="30"><b>#</b></td><td><b>File</b></td>
   </tr>
   <tr>
     <td>1</td><td>plazma-client-lite-&lt;version&gt;-win32-installer.exe</td>
   </tr>
   <tr>
     <td>2</td><td>plazma-server-lite-&lt;version&gt;-win32-installer.jar</td>
   </tr>

   </table>


   <br><br><br><br>

   <b>Linux (Standalone)</b> <br><br>


   <table width="100%">
   <tr>
     <td width="30"><b>#</b></td><td><b>File</b></td>
   </tr>
   <tr>
     <td>1</td><td>plazma-&lt;version&gt;-linux-gtk-installer.jar</td>
   </tr>
   </table>


   <br><br>

   <b>Linux (Lite Server)</b> <br><br>


   <table width="100%">
   <tr>
     <td width="30"><b>#</b></td><td><b>File</b></td>
   </tr>
   <tr>
     <td>1</td><td>plazma-client-lite-&lt;version&gt;-linux-gtk-installer.jar</td>
   </tr>
   <tr>
     <td>2</td><td>plazma-server-lite-&lt;version&gt;-linux-gtk-installer.jar</td>
   </tr>

   </table>


   
   <br><br>
   &lt;version&gt; - version of the Plazma, for example 0.1.8





   <br><br><br><br>


   <h3 align="center">Installation</h3>

   <b>Windows</b> <br><br>

   Depending on the file type of the installation, you have to do following:

   <br>
   <b>.exe</b> - run the file

   <br>
   <b>.jar</b> - run the command: <b>java -jar &lt;name of the jar file&gt;</b>



   <br><br>

   <b>Linux</b> <br><br>

   run the command: <b>java -jar &lt;name of the jar file&gt;</b>


   <br><br><br><br>


   If you choose installation using the application server (Lite Server), 
   you have to first run the server installation, and then run the client installation.<br><br>



   <br><br><br><br>

   <h3 align="center">Run application</h3>

   To run <b>Standalone</b> or <b>Client</b> application you have to do follow actions:<br><br><br>
   <b>Windows</b><br><br>
   Menu: Start -&gt; Programs -&gt; Plazma ERP+CRM &lt;version&gt; -&gt; Plazma ERP+CRM<br><br><br>

   or run the command file<br><br>

   <code>plazma.bat</code><br><br><br>

   or run the command<br><br>
   <code>javaw -Djava.library.path="lib\swt\win32" -jar launcher.jar plazma</code><br><br><br>



   <b>Linux</b><br><br>
   run the command file<br><br>

   <code>plazma.sh</code><br><br><br>
   or run the command<br><br>
   <code>java -Djava.library.path="lib/swt/linux-gtk" -jar launcher.jar plazma</code><br><br><br>

<b>IMPORTANT!</b> If you choose installation using the application server (Lite Server), you have to first run the server, and then the client. 

<br>
   For more information see <a target="main" href="../startup/index.html">Getting Started</a>
   


  <br><br><br><br>To start the <b>Lite Server</b> you have to run the command file:<br>


  <br><b>Windows</b><br><br>

  &lt;PlazmaLiteServer&gt;/start_server.bat

  <br>
  <br><b>Linux</b><br><br>

  &lt;PlazmaLiteServer&gt;/start_server.sh


   <br><br><br><br>

